import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="height", y="height", data=data, estimator=lambda x: len(x) / len(data) * 100)
    ax.axvline(data['height'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Height: {:.2f}'.format(data['height'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="name", data=data, palette="Set3")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title("What is the most common name in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
